1
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:16,633
I can't leave my mom.

2
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:18,367
I'm sorry.

3
00:00:18,433 --> 00:00:19,833
I'm sorry.

4
00:00:19,900 --> 00:00:21,433
Please!

5
00:00:21,500 --> 00:00:22,100
Yen!

6
00:00:22,167 --> 00:00:23,567
You saw how broken she was

7
00:00:23,633 --> 00:00:25,300
when she found out her daughter
was pregnant.

8
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:28,633
If I knew you would do
this to me,

9
00:00:28,700 --> 00:00:31,667
I wish I'd died in jail.

10
00:00:31,733 --> 00:00:33,633
And it's even more painful

11
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:37,633
because her enemy's son
is the baby's father.

12
00:00:37,733 --> 00:00:41,167
I still have a lot of plans
for our future.

13
00:00:41,233 --> 00:00:43,067
But it will never happen now.

14
00:00:43,133 --> 00:00:44,567
What do you want to do?

15
00:00:44,633 --> 00:00:46,467
Forget your own daughter?

16
00:00:46,533 --> 00:00:47,833
Disown her?

17
00:00:47,900 --> 00:00:49,200
I can live without her.

18
00:00:49,733 --> 00:00:53,800
- Mom, forgive me.
- Go with your boyfriend!

19
00:00:53,867 --> 00:00:57,267
I'll start getting used
to a life without you!

20
00:00:58,133 --> 00:01:01,267
Mom!

21
00:01:01,333 --> 00:01:03,200
Let's talk, Mom.

22
00:01:03,267 --> 00:01:05,133
Mom!

23
00:01:05,200 --> 00:01:05,600
Yen!

24
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:07,567
Yen, I'm here.

25
00:01:08,367 --> 00:01:09,400
Come with me.

26
00:01:09,467 --> 00:01:11,633
My mom hates me even more, Red.

27
00:01:11,700 --> 00:01:14,400
She won't accept me as her
daughter anymore.

28
00:01:14,467 --> 00:01:16,800
Now that everyone knows
our situation,

29
00:01:16,867 --> 00:01:18,833
I will take good care
of you more than ever.

30
00:01:18,900 --> 00:01:20,200
You and our baby.

31
00:01:20,267 --> 00:01:24,400
If they can't accept us,
we still have each other.

32
00:01:24,467 --> 00:01:25,933
Mom, please.

33
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:29,233
If you're here to cause trouble,
just leave, Mom. Please.

34
00:01:29,300 --> 00:01:33,333
This is an apology for
what my son did to you.

35
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:36,733
And I'm asking you
to forgive me.

36
00:01:37,733 --> 00:01:41,267
And in return,
I will take care of you.

37
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:02,933
Let's see if it
looks good on you.

38
00:02:03,933 --> 00:02:07,333
It's pretty.
It suits you very well.

39
00:02:07,400 --> 00:02:11,400
Mom, why are you still
calling me Yenyen?

40
00:02:11,467 --> 00:02:12,267
Why not?

41
00:02:12,967 --> 00:02:15,900
You will be my baby forever.

42
00:02:42,267 --> 00:02:47,967
Amanda, maybe we can talk now.

43
00:02:50,500 --> 00:02:54,967
I'm going to Cebu
the day after tomorrow.

44
00:02:56,567 --> 00:03:01,100
My company will send me
there to work for a month.

45
00:03:03,900 --> 00:03:08,100
I don't want to leave
you in this situation.

46
00:03:11,633 --> 00:03:14,767
Amanda, I think I have
the right to say something

47
00:03:14,833 --> 00:03:18,200
since I took care of her
for a long time.

48
00:03:20,067 --> 00:03:21,833
I don't want to talk
about it anymore.

49
00:03:24,267 --> 00:03:25,233
I'm tired.

50
00:03:26,767 --> 00:03:28,067
I want to get some rest.

51
00:03:30,233 --> 00:03:31,700
Can you get some rest?

52
00:03:32,867 --> 00:03:35,333
Not knowing where your
daughter's staying

53
00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:37,033
or what she's doing?

54
00:03:39,633 --> 00:03:47,233
Can you sleep feeling
miserable and mad?

55
00:03:49,867 --> 00:03:53,567
So you don't care
about your daughter.

56
00:03:57,467 --> 00:03:58,733
How can you do this?

57
00:04:00,200 --> 00:04:04,567
Are you really not worried
about your daughter?

58
00:04:07,300 --> 00:04:10,300
When she had a relationship
with Rina's son,

59
00:04:10,367 --> 00:04:11,533
did she think about me?

60
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:15,333
Did she consider
how I would feel?

61
00:04:16,333 --> 00:04:17,667
When they met on the island,

62
00:04:17,733 --> 00:04:21,733
she didn't know that Red
was Rina's son.

63
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:25,567
She didn't plan to get
stranded with him...

64
00:04:27,567 --> 00:04:32,867
and receive help from him
to survive,

65
00:04:32,933 --> 00:04:34,800
so she could return to you,
Amanda.

66
00:04:35,900 --> 00:04:38,033
I wish I had just rotted in jail

67
00:04:38,100 --> 00:04:39,533
if this was what my life
would be like.

68
00:04:45,167 --> 00:04:49,000
You won't understand me because
you don't know how I feel.

69
00:04:50,833 --> 00:04:53,533
And you don't know
what it feels like

70
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:56,100
to get betrayed by your child!

71
00:04:57,200 --> 00:04:58,633
You don't know that!

72
00:05:22,633 --> 00:05:24,567
Come in. Here we are!

73
00:05:26,333 --> 00:05:28,633
Welcome to your new home.

74
00:05:30,700 --> 00:05:32,633
Rina, what's going on?

75
00:05:33,467 --> 00:05:36,600
Well, Victor,
I brought Red home.

76
00:05:36,700 --> 00:05:39,067
But this time, with Eden.

77
00:05:40,167 --> 00:05:41,967
She'll be staying here with us.

78
00:05:44,967 --> 00:05:46,933
It's not that I'm against this,
but...

79
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:51,767
won't it be a problem once
Amanda finds out about this?

80
00:05:51,833 --> 00:05:54,033
Her mom abandoned her.

81
00:05:54,100 --> 00:05:56,300
I can't do that to her too.

82
00:05:56,367 --> 00:05:59,800
And besides, she is carrying
our grandchild.

83
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:04,467
I don't want to cause you
any trouble.

84
00:06:04,533 --> 00:06:06,600
I don't need to stay here.

85
00:06:06,667 --> 00:06:07,633
Yen, no.

86
00:06:07,733 --> 00:06:09,000
I won't let you leave,

87
00:06:09,067 --> 00:06:10,767
especially with how you are
right now.

88
00:06:11,633 --> 00:06:16,800
It's fine with me as long as
there won't be any problem.

89
00:06:16,867 --> 00:06:19,600
I hope your mom won't make
a big deal out of this.

90
00:06:21,067 --> 00:06:22,567
Thank you for understanding,
Dad.

91
00:06:24,233 --> 00:06:25,600
Look at the two of you.

92
00:06:26,167 --> 00:06:29,300
Goodness,
you're being sentimental now?

93
00:06:32,833 --> 00:06:34,800
Okay, I'll bring Yenyen to my
room.

94
00:06:38,667 --> 00:06:39,967
Red, no!

95
00:06:40,033 --> 00:06:40,433
No.

96
00:06:45,567 --> 00:06:47,333
You are not taking
her to your room.

97
00:06:51,900 --> 00:06:53,833
What do you mean Yenyen won't
stay in my room?

98
00:06:56,400 --> 00:06:57,667
What I mean is she's...

99
00:06:58,533 --> 00:07:00,967
she's staying in another room.

100
00:07:02,033 --> 00:07:03,500
Another room?

101
00:07:03,567 --> 00:07:05,233
Come, I'll show you. Follow me.

102
00:07:07,100 --> 00:07:07,633
Come on.

103
00:07:17,033 --> 00:07:18,067
This...

104
00:07:20,067 --> 00:07:22,167
this is going to be your room,
okay?

105
00:07:22,233 --> 00:07:23,700
You're staying in
the guest room.

106
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:27,033
Mom, why can't she
stay in my room?

107
00:07:27,100 --> 00:07:29,100
That way, I can look after her.

108
00:07:29,167 --> 00:07:34,333
Red, I don't think it's proper
for the two of you

109
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:35,700
to stay in one room
because you're not married yet.

110
00:07:37,833 --> 00:07:39,067
Your mom is right, Red.

111
00:07:42,367 --> 00:07:45,067
I don't want our friends
to think

112
00:07:45,133 --> 00:07:51,733
we're letting you stay together
in one room.

113
00:07:52,633 --> 00:07:56,800
What matters now is that
Eden is here,

114
00:07:56,867 --> 00:07:58,333
and we can look after her.

115
00:08:00,367 --> 00:08:01,400
That's okay, Red.

116
00:08:01,467 --> 00:08:04,700
It's for our own good and
for your family's sake.

117
00:08:07,933 --> 00:08:13,100
Thank you for accepting
my future child and me.

118
00:08:14,067 --> 00:08:18,400
And sorry for causing you
trouble.

119
00:08:19,367 --> 00:08:24,100
I'm sorry because Red fell
in love with me, of all people.

120
00:08:26,667 --> 00:08:27,367
Eden...

121
00:08:31,567 --> 00:08:33,933
will you please
stop saying sorry?

122
00:08:35,400 --> 00:08:40,533
It's me, who should apologize.

123
00:08:42,167 --> 00:08:44,300
After everything that
I've done to you...

124
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:49,333
can we just forget everything
that happened between us?

125
00:08:50,900 --> 00:08:53,800
For my grandchild's sake?

126
00:08:58,867 --> 00:09:03,900
And maybe this is a blessing
in disguise.

127
00:09:04,967 --> 00:09:09,933
We lost Angelo,
and we only have Red...

128
00:09:10,367 --> 00:09:13,967
but now we're about
to have a grandchild.

129
00:09:15,933 --> 00:09:17,633
And you're carrying him.

130
00:10:26,767 --> 00:10:29,667
Me and Yenyen love each other!

131
00:10:33,033 --> 00:10:35,133
What is this guy talking about?

132
00:10:35,233 --> 00:10:36,667
Are you in a relationship
with him?

133
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:39,133
Mom...

134
00:10:42,733 --> 00:10:43,767
Stop crying.

135
00:10:44,533 --> 00:10:45,400
Answer me.

136
00:10:50,267 --> 00:10:52,200
Red is my boyfriend, Mom.

137
00:11:32,667 --> 00:11:34,367
Mom, I'm pregnant.

138
00:11:36,700 --> 00:11:38,067
Red is the father of my child.

139
00:11:52,033 --> 00:11:52,667
Mom.

140
00:11:53,533 --> 00:11:55,567
Mom, I'm sorry.

141
00:11:55,633 --> 00:11:56,533
Please forgive, Mom.

142
00:11:56,600 --> 00:12:00,133
You should go with your
boyfriend!

143
00:12:01,500 --> 00:12:03,067
They need you more than I do!

144
00:12:07,533 --> 00:12:08,533
It hurts!

145
00:12:10,033 --> 00:12:11,200
Mom!

146
00:12:11,267 --> 00:12:14,100
But I'll start getting used
to living without you!

147
00:12:14,667 --> 00:12:16,500
Mom!

148
00:12:16,567 --> 00:12:26,533
- Mom, no!
- Amanda, please stop!

149
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:41,467
- Mom, no!
- Amanda, please stop!

150
00:12:59,500 --> 00:13:00,900
Yenyen!

151
00:13:04,033 --> 00:13:04,633
Eden!

152
00:13:04,700 --> 00:13:05,700
Mom!

153
00:13:05,767 --> 00:13:06,700
Eden!

154
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:08,467
Eden!

155
00:13:08,533 --> 00:13:09,300
Mom!
Eden!

156
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:11,400
Mom!

157
00:13:13,533 --> 00:13:14,567
You're alive!

158
00:13:20,633 --> 00:13:21,900
Yen, it's me.

159
00:13:22,733 --> 00:13:24,467
Red, come in.

160
00:13:29,567 --> 00:13:30,867
I'm just checking on you.

161
00:13:31,767 --> 00:13:33,033
Are you sure you're okay here?

162
00:13:47,200 --> 00:13:49,333
Are you still thinking
about your mom?

163
00:13:53,067 --> 00:13:55,700
Yen, I understand
how you're feeling.

164
00:13:57,133 --> 00:14:02,100
Maybe we should give your mom
a chance to absorb everything.

165
00:14:02,167 --> 00:14:04,633
Because that's what
my mom and dad did.

166
00:14:05,533 --> 00:14:06,500
They accepted us after
everything.

167
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:09,433
I'm sure the time will come

168
00:14:09,500 --> 00:14:12,733
when your mom realizes she can't
abandon you...

169
00:14:13,633 --> 00:14:15,000
just like what my mom did.

170
00:14:15,967 --> 00:14:18,400
Once she realizes she's going
to have a grandchild...

171
00:14:19,267 --> 00:14:21,500
I'm sure she'll change her mind.

172
00:14:23,967 --> 00:14:25,100
I hope you're right.

173
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:34,233
When I saw how your parents
accepted our situation,

174
00:14:34,300 --> 00:14:35,800
I was envious.

175
00:14:37,633 --> 00:14:43,900
Even though it's hard to believe
your mom's change of heart...

176
00:14:46,500 --> 00:14:49,233
actually, I still have
doubts up until now.

177
00:14:50,900 --> 00:14:54,600
But I'll still give her
a chance,

178
00:14:54,667 --> 00:14:57,667
the same way she gave me
a chance.

179
00:15:00,367 --> 00:15:01,300
She's understanding,

180
00:15:03,167 --> 00:15:04,600
while my mom is...

181
00:15:04,667 --> 00:15:05,300
Yen.

182
00:15:13,500 --> 00:15:18,367
All I care about now
is our baby's safety.

183
00:15:21,667 --> 00:15:22,900
I won't give up on her.

184
00:15:28,933 --> 00:15:30,133
Yes, yes, Mr. Akashi.

185
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:31,133
Thank you, thank you, Sir.

186
00:15:31,200 --> 00:15:32,500
Thank you very much, Sir.

187
00:15:34,033 --> 00:15:36,133
Mr. Akashi's happy with us.

188
00:15:36,233 --> 00:15:38,700
But we need to set a meeting
with him to...

189
00:15:39,933 --> 00:15:40,400
Rina?

190
00:15:41,500 --> 00:15:43,133
Looks like you're thinking
a lot about something.

191
00:15:44,100 --> 00:15:45,133
Is it about Eden?

192
00:15:46,567 --> 00:15:49,467
Speaking of which,
is what I saw earlier real?

193
00:15:49,533 --> 00:15:51,367
Do you really care for Eden?

194
00:15:52,500 --> 00:15:54,033
Can you please pass
me the alcohol?

195
00:15:55,133 --> 00:15:58,633
Hurry! I want to get rid of the
germs I got from touching her.

196
00:16:01,767 --> 00:16:02,467
Do you think...

197
00:16:03,267 --> 00:16:05,900
I'll accept her just like that?

198
00:16:05,967 --> 00:16:07,633
Never! No way!

199
00:16:08,967 --> 00:16:11,633
Even if she's carrying
my grandchild...

200
00:16:13,133 --> 00:16:15,167
she is still Amanda's daughter.

201
00:16:15,233 --> 00:16:16,933
I can't accept her.

202
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:18,567
So you were just faking?

203
00:16:19,733 --> 00:16:21,900
Wow! You were so believable.

204
00:16:21,967 --> 00:16:23,433
You're such a good actress.

205
00:16:23,500 --> 00:16:25,100
Best actress!

206
00:16:25,167 --> 00:16:26,933
And Eden is my award.

207
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:33,100
I will continue poisoning
her mind against her mom.

208
00:16:35,367 --> 00:16:38,333
I saw how devastated Amanda was,

209
00:16:39,267 --> 00:16:43,867
when Eden lied to her,
when she got betrayed.

210
00:16:45,567 --> 00:16:48,100
I will keep destroying Amanda.

211
00:16:51,300 --> 00:16:54,767
This is the revenge
I've been waiting for.

212
00:16:57,433 --> 00:17:00,200
She took my son away from me
when she killed him.

213
00:17:02,133 --> 00:17:02,967
Well now...

214
00:17:04,433 --> 00:17:06,433
I'm going to take her
daughter away from her.

215
00:17:08,633 --> 00:17:13,400
Until the day she loses her for
good.

216
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:21,767
What do you mean we're having
a problem with the investors?

217
00:17:23,667 --> 00:17:25,867
Set up a meeting,
and then we'll discuss it.

218
00:17:28,433 --> 00:17:29,400
What's going on?

219
00:17:30,567 --> 00:17:32,400
We're having a problem
with one of the investors.

220
00:17:32,467 --> 00:17:34,333
But don't worry, I'll fix it.

221
00:17:38,100 --> 00:17:39,100
Oh!

222
00:17:39,167 --> 00:17:40,100
There you are.

223
00:17:43,300 --> 00:17:44,367
- Eden.
- Good morning, guys.

224
00:17:44,433 --> 00:17:45,033
Good morning.

225
00:17:45,100 --> 00:17:46,233
Good morning.

226
00:17:46,300 --> 00:17:48,300
How was your first
night in your room?

227
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:49,767
It's okay.

228
00:17:49,833 --> 00:17:51,000
Thank you.

229
00:17:51,067 --> 00:17:52,400
Join us for breakfast.

230
00:17:53,033 --> 00:17:53,800
Wow!

231
00:17:57,100 --> 00:17:58,100
Good morning.

232
00:18:00,133 --> 00:18:02,133
So, you had a good night?

233
00:18:02,200 --> 00:18:03,400
That's good to know.

234
00:18:06,133 --> 00:18:06,567
Red?

235
00:18:10,300 --> 00:18:11,033
What's this for?

236
00:18:12,033 --> 00:18:14,300
I want you to take
Eden shopping.

237
00:18:14,367 --> 00:18:15,500
She doesn't have
anything with her.

238
00:18:15,567 --> 00:18:17,333
She doesn't have clothes,
so you should go shopping.

239
00:18:24,533 --> 00:18:28,233
And I also called up
Dr. Villegas, my OB-GYN.

240
00:18:28,300 --> 00:18:30,933
Of course, I want my grandchild
to get checked up.

241
00:18:32,100 --> 00:18:33,800
And you, too, Eden.

242
00:18:35,633 --> 00:18:36,733
Thank you.

243
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:39,600
I really appreciate your help.

244
00:18:40,867 --> 00:18:42,833
Don't mention it. Come on, Eden.

245
00:18:43,633 --> 00:18:48,467
Of course, I'm doing all of this
for my son, Red

246
00:18:48,533 --> 00:18:50,167
and my grandchild.

247
00:18:51,700 --> 00:18:53,633
And that includes you, too,
Eden.

248
00:18:56,100 --> 00:18:58,900
Guys, I don't know what to say.

249
00:18:59,800 --> 00:19:00,533
Thank you.

250
00:19:01,767 --> 00:19:03,333
I love you! Thank you!

251
00:19:04,567 --> 00:19:06,100
Thank you, Dad.

252
00:19:12,933 --> 00:19:16,333
Based on the test we've done,
you are five weeks pregnant.

253
00:19:19,667 --> 00:19:21,167
In the first trimester,

254
00:19:21,233 --> 00:19:23,167
you will experience some
discomforts

255
00:19:23,233 --> 00:19:29,333
like morning sickness,
dizziness, or feeling exhausted.

256
00:19:29,433 --> 00:19:31,233
But it's just normal.

257
00:19:32,667 --> 00:19:36,033
The first trimester of pregnancy
is very fragile.

258
00:19:36,867 --> 00:19:40,367
That's why you really have
to take care of yourself, Eden.

259
00:19:41,400 --> 00:19:42,800
Don't worry, Doc.

260
00:19:42,867 --> 00:19:46,433
I'll do everything to have
a safe pregnancy.

261
00:19:46,500 --> 00:19:48,900
I will prescribe vitamins
and supplements

262
00:19:48,967 --> 00:19:50,200
for you and the baby, okay?

263
00:19:50,267 --> 00:19:51,100
Okay.

264
00:19:52,667 --> 00:19:54,000
We're going to have a baby.

265
00:19:54,067 --> 00:19:54,633
Yes.

266
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:02,800
I don't understand how
I feel right now, Red.

267
00:20:03,667 --> 00:20:07,000
I feel happy, but it seems
like something is missing.

268
00:20:08,033 --> 00:20:13,733
Maybe I'll be happier
if my mom is here.

269
00:20:13,800 --> 00:20:18,533
I want to share all these
special moments with her.

270
00:20:18,600 --> 00:20:19,333
But...

271
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:22,367
Yen, don't think about it, okay?

272
00:20:23,467 --> 00:20:26,567
As the doctor said,
we have to prioritize our baby.

273
00:20:27,733 --> 00:20:28,733
Don't worry.

274
00:20:28,800 --> 00:20:31,167
One of these days,
your mom will be with you.

275
00:20:33,533 --> 00:20:34,300
Here you go.

276
00:20:35,100 --> 00:20:36,633
Make sure you get everything
I prescribed

277
00:20:36,700 --> 00:20:38,333
and take it regularly, okay?

278
00:20:38,400 --> 00:20:39,700
Okay.

279
00:20:39,767 --> 00:20:40,633
We got this.

280
00:20:56,033 --> 00:20:56,667
Amanda...

281
00:20:57,500 --> 00:20:59,933
are you sure you'll be
okay here?

282
00:21:02,267 --> 00:21:04,733
If I didn't get assigned
in Cebu,

283
00:21:04,800 --> 00:21:05,933
I wouldn't leave you here
by yourself...

284
00:21:06,633 --> 00:21:08,467
especially now that
Eden's not here.

285
00:21:09,933 --> 00:21:13,667
Don't worry about me.
I can handle myself.

286
00:21:14,633 --> 00:21:17,567
Amanda, why don't
you talk to her?

287
00:21:18,967 --> 00:21:20,633
I talked to Eden earlier.

288
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:24,100
Do you know where
she is right now?

289
00:21:24,167 --> 00:21:26,067
Didn't I tell you I don't
want to talk about her?

290
00:21:27,367 --> 00:21:30,567
It's okay that your daughter is
far away from you, Amanda?

291
00:21:33,300 --> 00:21:35,833
Amanda, I talked to Eden
earlier.

292
00:21:35,900 --> 00:21:37,200
Do you know where she is?

293
00:21:37,267 --> 00:21:38,800
I don't care.

294
00:21:38,867 --> 00:21:40,300
She's staying at Rina's house.

295
00:21:41,167 --> 00:21:42,367
Red took her there.

296
00:21:44,633 --> 00:21:45,500
What?
How did that happen?

297
00:21:47,867 --> 00:21:49,833
Rina and Victor finally accepted
her.

298
00:21:50,567 --> 00:21:52,233
Eden doesn't have a choice,
right?

299
00:21:53,167 --> 00:21:55,367
You kicked her out.
Where will she stay?

300
00:21:55,433 --> 00:21:56,567
But why there?

301
00:21:56,633 --> 00:21:57,633
Isn't she thinking?

302
00:21:58,400 --> 00:22:00,767
They will just mistreat her
there!

303
00:22:00,833 --> 00:22:02,767
They will take revenge on her.

304
00:22:02,833 --> 00:22:08,000
Eden is old enough.
She knows what she's doing.

305
00:22:08,067 --> 00:22:09,367
I won't let that happen.

306
00:22:09,433 --> 00:22:12,333
And I don't believe
Rina can accept her.

307
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:13,000
No!

308
00:22:19,767 --> 00:22:21,000
What can I do for you, Ma'am?

309
00:22:21,067 --> 00:22:23,200
I need to see Eden, my daughter.

310
00:22:23,267 --> 00:22:25,067
I need to talk to her.

311
00:22:25,133 --> 00:22:26,100
Ma'am Eden?

312
00:22:26,167 --> 00:22:27,500
She's not here.

313
00:22:27,567 --> 00:22:29,533
She went out with Sir Red.

314
00:22:29,600 --> 00:22:32,267
I don't believe you.
I know she's here.

315
00:22:32,333 --> 00:22:34,633
Let me see my daughter.
I want to talk to her.

316
00:22:34,700 --> 00:22:36,300
Ma'am, she's not here.

317
00:22:36,367 --> 00:22:38,633
Just leave if you don't
want to believe me.

318
00:22:39,767 --> 00:22:42,867
I'm not leaving until
I see my daughter.

319
00:22:43,500 --> 00:22:45,600
Maám, Eden is really not here.

320
00:22:45,667 --> 00:22:46,533
You're lying.

321
00:22:47,267 --> 00:22:48,900
You're hiding my daughter.

322
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:50,133
Let me see my daughter.

323
00:22:51,133 --> 00:22:52,533
Will it be okay with your dad?

324
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:55,333
I think we bought
a little too much.

325
00:22:55,400 --> 00:22:56,800
Yen, don't think about it.

326
00:22:56,867 --> 00:22:58,533
He won't mind.

327
00:22:58,600 --> 00:23:00,333
You're no stranger to us.

328
00:23:00,400 --> 00:23:02,233
And besides, we're having
a baby together.

329
00:23:02,300 --> 00:23:04,500
Automatically, you're
part of the family.

330
00:23:04,567 --> 00:23:05,667
Thank you, Red.

331
00:23:05,733 --> 00:23:10,067
You kept your promise that
you'll take care of me.

332
00:23:10,133 --> 00:23:13,100
Don't worry.
I'll keep my promise too.

333
00:23:13,167 --> 00:23:15,233
I'll take good care
of our baby too.

334
00:23:20,233 --> 00:23:21,333
Is that my mom?

335
00:23:25,967 --> 00:23:26,700
Mom!

336
00:23:28,333 --> 00:23:29,033
Eden.

337
00:23:29,100 --> 00:23:30,533
Mom, what are you doing here?

338
00:23:31,500 --> 00:23:32,567
Miss Amanda.

339
00:23:32,633 --> 00:23:35,200
Come on, Eden. Let's go home.
Come home with me.

340
00:23:35,267 --> 00:23:35,967
Let's go.

341
00:23:36,033 --> 00:23:37,433
Mom, wait. You're hurting me.

342
00:23:37,500 --> 00:23:39,300
- Miss Amanda, can you please?
- What?

343
00:23:39,367 --> 00:23:40,533
Please what?

344
00:23:40,600 --> 00:23:43,333
Stay out of this!
Leave us alone!

345
00:23:43,400 --> 00:23:46,033
I'm taking her away from
you and your family!

346
00:23:46,100 --> 00:23:49,333
Mom, wait.
Can we talk about this?

347
00:23:49,400 --> 00:23:52,000
Ma'am Rina has already
accepted my baby.

348
00:23:52,067 --> 00:23:55,800
I hope you can too.
Let's fix this problem.

349
00:23:55,900 --> 00:23:56,767
What are you trying to say?

350
00:23:56,833 --> 00:23:59,067
Are you saying they
are good people?

351
00:23:59,133 --> 00:24:00,833
And I'm the bad guy here?

352
00:24:00,900 --> 00:24:04,033
Eden, do you think Rina
can accept you?

353
00:24:04,100 --> 00:24:06,200
Wake up!

354
00:24:06,267 --> 00:24:09,667
His family will never love you!

355
00:24:09,733 --> 00:24:16,367
Mom, listen to me, please,
for your grandchild's sake.

356
00:24:16,433 --> 00:24:17,967
I can't accept this!

357
00:24:18,033 --> 00:24:19,933
As long as you're
with his family,

358
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:22,067
I will never have peace of mind.

359
00:24:22,133 --> 00:24:23,667
Come on, let's go home.

360
00:24:23,733 --> 00:24:25,033
Let's talk about
this on our own.

361
00:24:25,100 --> 00:24:27,000
Just the two of us.

362
00:24:27,067 --> 00:24:28,400
Listen to me, Eden.

363
00:24:29,267 --> 00:24:31,533
I'm your mom.
You have to listen to me.

364
00:24:31,600 --> 00:24:32,900
Mom.

365
00:24:32,967 --> 00:24:33,800
Please, Eden.

366
00:24:33,867 --> 00:24:37,133
Mom, I can't deny
Red of his right.

367
00:24:38,100 --> 00:24:40,200
I grew up without a father.

368
00:24:41,233 --> 00:24:43,800
I don't want that to
happen to my child.

369
00:24:43,867 --> 00:24:44,767
Eden.

370
00:24:44,833 --> 00:24:46,633
Come with me.

371
00:24:46,700 --> 00:24:48,100
Let's get out of here.

372
00:24:49,767 --> 00:24:50,833
Come on, Eden.

373
00:24:52,100 --> 00:24:53,467
So it's true, Auntie?

374
00:24:53,533 --> 00:24:55,433
Will Red not be going
to the US anymore?

375
00:24:56,467 --> 00:24:57,267
Why?

376
00:24:58,433 --> 00:25:03,100
Let's just say it's some
kind of a family issue.

377
00:25:06,567 --> 00:25:08,567
What's taking Emma so long?

378
00:25:08,633 --> 00:25:09,933
I just asked her to pick
up something at the gate.

379
00:25:10,000 --> 00:25:12,900
And she's still not back.
It's taking her forever.

380
00:25:12,967 --> 00:25:16,133
Can you imagine?
I had to order something online.

381
00:25:16,200 --> 00:25:18,100
For Red, to make him happy.

382
00:25:19,033 --> 00:25:23,000
Why would you do that, Auntie?
Is there an occasion?

383
00:25:23,067 --> 00:25:25,733
No, actually, it's for Eden.

384
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:28,200
She lives here now.

385
00:25:31,833 --> 00:25:32,467
What?

386
00:25:35,200 --> 00:25:36,167
Miss Amanda...

387
00:25:37,733 --> 00:25:40,200
my family accepted
our situation.

388
00:25:41,167 --> 00:25:42,500
If you can't accept us,

389
00:25:42,567 --> 00:25:46,433
we'll give you time
to process everything.

390
00:25:46,500 --> 00:25:47,767
But I hope you realize

391
00:25:47,833 --> 00:25:51,800
that you will have to accept our
child if you love your daughter.

392
00:25:51,867 --> 00:25:56,400
And who are you to tell me
how to love my daughter?

393
00:25:57,367 --> 00:25:58,600
It's all your fault!

394
00:25:59,400 --> 00:26:00,267
Mom!

395
00:26:00,333 --> 00:26:02,767
This is all your fault!

396
00:26:02,833 --> 00:26:05,467
- Mom, please don't hurt Red.
- It's you!

397
00:26:05,533 --> 00:26:07,067
You bastard!

398
00:26:07,133 --> 00:26:10,133
I still can't believe that
Red got Yenyen pregnant.

399
00:26:10,233 --> 00:26:12,700
Well, if you cared
for him enough,

400
00:26:12,767 --> 00:26:15,233
we won't have this problem.

401
00:26:15,300 --> 00:26:18,633
Plus, I don't have to be
pretending that I like Eden.

402
00:26:18,700 --> 00:26:20,300
What do you mean, Auntie?

403
00:26:20,367 --> 00:26:24,333
I must say that your condition
is critical, Eden.

404
00:26:24,400 --> 00:26:25,900
You had profuse bleeding.

405
00:26:25,967 --> 00:26:28,933
You should avoid
strenuous activities

406
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:31,167
for your baby's welfare.

407
00:26:31,233 --> 00:26:33,033
Something happened between
the two of you

408
00:26:33,100 --> 00:26:34,467
while we were on the island.

409
00:26:34,533 --> 00:26:35,767
Whatever happened between us,

410
00:26:35,833 --> 00:26:36,733
you have nothing to do with it.

411
00:26:36,800 --> 00:26:40,033
I just don't know
how to accept this.

412
00:26:40,100 --> 00:26:43,800
You have to think about
what matters to you the most.

413
00:26:43,900 --> 00:26:47,300
Is it your mom or your baby?
